OL,3,C'Real possibility' jailed PC was
OL,4,Cvictim of miscarriage of justice
OL,6,FMr Major, who was a PC with West
OL,7,FYorkshire Police, was accused of
OL,8,Fattacking a drunken 18-year-old in the
OL,9,Fvan dock and a cell at Bridewell
OL,10,FPolice Station in Leeds in the early
OL,11,Fhours of 6 September 2003.
OL,13,FA jury failed to reach a verdict at an
OL,14,Finitial trial in April 2006, but Mr
OL,15,FMajor was convicted at a retrial the
OL,16,Fsame year. He served four months of
OL,17,Fhis 15-month prison sentence.
OL,19,FAfter leaving prison his family
OL,20,Fstarted a campaign to have his
OL,21,Fconviction overturned.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/5
